17:22.843 --> 17:25.811
Look at the two of us.

17:25.814 --> 17:28.831
Me, a highly
regarded physicist.

17:28.833 --> 17:31.017
The kind of mind that
comes along once,

17:31.019 --> 17:33.102
maybe twice in a generation.

17:33.104 --> 17:35.504
You, the common man,

17:35.506 --> 17:39.142
tired from your labors
as a stockbroker,

17:39.144 --> 17:43.346
or vacuum cleaner salesman,
or bootblack.

17:44.848 --> 17:47.516
But deep down inside...

17:47.518 --> 17:50.153
apparently we're just
two peas in a pod.

17:50.155 --> 17:53.206
A regular pea,

17:53.208 --> 17:55.875
and the kind of pea
that comes along once,

17:55.877 --> 17:58.244
maybe twice in a generation.

18:02.500 --> 18:03.699
Rain.

18:03.701 --> 18:06.135
Another great equalizer.

18:06.137 --> 18:08.004
Falling on the head
of the brilliant

18:08.006 --> 18:10.139
and the unremarkable alike.

18:17.181 --> 18:19.382
Smarty-pants.

18:22.853 --> 18:25.221
Oh, Mrs. Cooper,
it smells so good.

18:25.223 --> 18:26.439
You take notes, darlin'.

18:26.441 --> 18:28.858
The real way to get a man
is with melted cheese

18:28.860 --> 18:30.660
and cream of mushroom soup.

18:30.662 --> 18:34.330
He'll die at 50 but
his love will be true.

18:39.003 --> 18:41.237
I need a tissue.
This one got wet.

18:44.408 --> 18:45.625
Here.

18:45.627 --> 18:49.178
Thank you. Yeah, I've
learned something today.

18:49.180 --> 18:53.049
You and I, in so many ways,

18:53.051 --> 18:56.352
other than intelligence and
what counts, we're the same.

18:58.589 --> 19:01.190
Sweetheart, are you sick?

19:01.192 --> 19:04.093
I hope so, because if this is
well, life isn't worth living.

19:04.095 --> 19:07.397
Oh, sugarpie,
you are burning up.

19:07.399 --> 19:09.649
- We've got to get you to bed.
- Okay.

19:09.651 --> 19:12.101
Don't worry. Mama's here
to take care of her baby.

19:12.103 --> 19:16.205
And just to be clear,
only her baby

19:16.207 --> 19:17.490
and not these other people.

19:17.492 --> 19:19.442
Of course.

19:19.444 --> 19:22.879
Can I have tea with honey and
toast with the crust cut off?

19:22.881 --> 19:25.498
You can have
whatever you want.

19:25.500 --> 19:28.384
Thanks, Mom.
You're the best.

19:39.741 --> 19:41.654
Boy, last time I put
VapoRub on you,

19:41.655 --> 19:44.606
you didn't have hair
on your chest.

19:44.608 --> 19:47.910
I know, it filled in last year.

19:49.963 --> 19:52.881
I didn't get to spend a lot of
time with you on this visit.

19:52.883 --> 19:54.967
And whose fault was that?

19:55.785 --> 19:57.953
Yours.

19:59.138 --> 20:01.306
Shelly, you're not eight
years old anymore.

20:01.308 --> 20:03.225
We have to have
a different relationship.

20:03.227 --> 20:05.143
No, we don't.

20:05.145 --> 20:06.645
The one we have
works great.

20:06.647 --> 20:08.347
Sweetheart, you are a grown man.

20:08.349 --> 20:10.799
Or maybe I'm part of
a new species,

20:10.801 --> 20:12.684
that lives for
hundreds of years,

20:12.686 --> 20:15.771
which means I'm still
basically a toddler.

20:15.773 --> 20:18.974
Oh, I so should have
taken you to Houston.

20:22.579 --> 20:24.997
Does this mean you're not
going to sing "Soft Kitty"?

20:24.999 --> 20:28.617
No, I will always
sing you "Soft Kitty."

20:29.669 --> 20:32.988
♪ Soft kitty, warm kitty ♪

20:32.990 --> 20:35.257
♪ Little ball of fur... ♪

20:35.259 --> 20:37.158
Mrs. Cooper, were we supposed to
take that pie out of the oven?

20:37.160 --> 20:39.962
Get out!

20:41.097 --> 20:42.097
Well, that was rude.

20:42.099 --> 20:45.333
Well, I know,
but he means well.

20:46.335 --> 20:47.636
Sing.

20:47.638 --> 20:51.189
♪ Happy kitty, sleepy kitty... ♪

20:51.191 --> 20:52.908
What are you trying
to pull, Mom?

20:52.910 --> 20:55.477
From the top.

20:55.479 --> 20:59.147
This is what I'm talking about.

20:59.149 --> 21:01.950
